What is method in Java:
A method is a block of code that contains the logic to solve a specific problem that
method all the instructions or logic inside this method executed.

A method can return something.
for example

int addAddReturn() {
int num1=30;
int num2=10;
return num1+num2;
}

How to choose what to use? Sysout or Return?
It depends on the requirement
Mostly we use and write methods that return data.